words, is it fair to say that you see these docks 
being built for the transport of oil in places like

24:43.596 --> 24:52.189
the Gulf here and the Gulf of California? I don't 
know if they're going to be docks. They're going to

24:53.271 --> 24:56.375
be monobuies of some sort, I think. Why should they 
be docks? But I see no reason. Well, one thing I

24:59.780 --> 25:01.122
really don't understand. You can perhaps 
elucidate me. Huh? What is the tremendous virtue

25:04.403 --> 25:07.047
of a free port? I mean, look at Hong Kong. Well, of 
course, now it's a special case because it's an

25:09.772 --> 25:14.920
outlet of goods from mainland China. But free 
ports around the world prosper tremendously.

25:19.868 --> 25:22.332
What happens if you have a free port right in the 
middle of the ocean somewhere? All the ships have

25:22.352 --> 25:24.034
to come in and trade goods. You can have a nuclear 
